The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has called for the enactment of new and modern laws for the smooth conduct of local government elections in the country. The INEC Chairman, Prof. Mahmood Yakubu, made the call on Thursday in Abuja at a meeting between INEC and the Forum of State Independent Electoral Commissions of Nigeria (FOSIECON). Apparently reacting to call for the abolition of the State Independent Electoral Commission (SIECs), Yakubu also said that the SIECs derived their mandates from the same section of the Constitution that INEC derives its mandate from. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY According to him, the commission would rather work with the SIECs to strengthen democracy in Nigeria and improve the conducts of elections in the country. Detail later…. IPAC wants SIECs scrapped IPAC demands scrapping of SIECs EU election observers’ report